texts.label: text
texts.orig: The overwhelming majority of Europeans eat meat, but most of them say they do not eat it every day.
texts.text: The overwhelming majority of Europeans eat meat, but most of them say they do not eat it every day.

texts.label: text
texts.orig: If the price of meat increased (for whatever reason) consumers would primarily react by buying cheaper types of meat and cuts and reducing their meat consumption.
texts.text: If the price of meat increased (for whatever reason) consumers would primarily react by buying cheaper types of meat and cuts and reducing their meat consumption.

texts.label: text
texts.orig: Consumers want more information on animal welfare. Three quarters of respondents agree with providing method-of-production labelling on all animal products, not just eggs as is currently the case.
texts.text: Consumers want more information on animal welfare. Three quarters of respondents agree with providing method-of-production labelling on all animal products, not just eggs as is currently the case.

texts.label: text
texts.orig: Animal welfare is an important issue for a very large majority of consumers. Around 9 in 10 consider important the implementation of new laws to improve the welfare of farmed animals such as providing more living space, banning cage systems, and mutilations.
texts.text: Animal welfare is an important issue for a very large majority of consumers. Around 9 in 10 consider important the implementation of new laws to improve the welfare of farmed animals such as providing more living space, banning cage systems, and mutilations.

texts.label: text
texts.orig: 7 in 10 consumers say that they are willing to pay more for food which is produced to higher welfare standards, although to a varying extent. Of those willing to pay more, half of them are only ready to pay up to 5% more, 30% are willing to pay up to 10% more, 12% are willing to pay up to 20% more and 8% are willing to pay more than 20% more. At the same time, around 17% say that they currently have serious difficulties dealing with the cost of meat.

texts.label: text
texts.orig: Still, method-of-production labelling for eggs could be improved as most consumers have either not noticed it ( 22% ) or do not understand such labels ( 33% ).
texts.text: Still, method-of-production labelling for eggs could be improved as most consumers have either not noticed it ( 22% ) or do not understand such labels ( 33% ).

texts.label: text
texts.orig: Consumers agree ( 76% ) that animal food imports should be subject to the same welfare rules as those produced in the EU while a strong majority ( 74% ) would like the EU to financially support farmers to apply higher animal welfare practices.
